items.title: Anthropic launches enterprise ‘Agent Skills’ and opens the standard, challenging OpenAI in workplace AI
items.summary: San Francisco-based artificial intelligence company Anthropic has released its Agent Skills technology as an open standard . Anthropic also unveiled organization-wide management tools for enterprise customers and a directory of partner-built skills from companies including Atlassian, Canva and Stripe . Microsoft has already adopted Agent Skills within VS Code and GitHub; so have popular coding agents like Cursor, Goose, Amp, OpenCode .
